Ordf. i tax:nd fr. 28, å hyr:nd:avd. fr. 42, i Emily Dicksons stift. fr. 40, i styr. f. Gbgs stads bef :-hav. änke- o. pup ikassa, i fÖTen. Sv:es stadsfogdar 47.
translated: Bengtsson, Nils Emanuel, first city bailiff of Gothenburg, born on April 11, 1892 in Lund to Lars B. and Anna Jönsson. Married to Karin Hallengren in 1925. They had two sons: Lars-Magnus born in 1927 and Nils-Göran born in 1928. Completed high school in 1910 and graduated with a law degree in 1914. Served as a substitute judge and clerk from 1915-1919. Became an authorized notary and magistrate of the town of Gothenburg in 1919, an assistant magistrate in 1923, and the first city bailiff from 1935. Also served as a secretary and representative for the Gothenburg port authority from 1925 and as chairman of several committees including the tax committee from 1928, the housing committee from 1942 and Emily Dickson's foundation from 1940. Additionally, he was on the board of directors for the Gothenburg city welfare fund for widows and orphans and for the Swedish bailiffs association from 1947.
